# [\#15237 Issue](https://github.com/ethereum/solidity/issues/15237) `closed`: Long statements can cause segmentation faults in IR-based codegen
**Labels**: `bug :bug:`


#### <img src="https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/76193362?u=4e8ae4cdf21413eec9e64a60a16dda14baf9a47f&v=4" width="50">[lum7na](https://github.com/lum7na) opened issue at [2024-07-02 09:19](https://github.com/ethereum/solidity/issues/15237):

## Description

A segmentation fault occurs when compiling the following code using IR-based codegen.

Compiling with `solc-0.8.26 a.sol --via-ir --bin`

```solidity
contract A {
  function f() public payable {
    bytes memory v = abi.encodePacked(bytes12(0x600b5981380380925939f3fe), hex"");
  }

}
```

I guess this could be due to excessively long statements. Legacy codegen does not encounter this issue.

## Environment

- Compiler version: 0.8.26

Thank you for reporting this! The issue was already fixed in PR #15209 and the fix will be available with the next release
